{{Infobox Organization |name = Kingston Bridal Week |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = {{Location map | Jamaica | width = | float = | border = | caption = | alt = | relief = | link = | lat_deg = 18.0106 | lon_deg = -76.7986 }} |motto = More than just a Bridal Show |formation = 2011 |type = Bridal Fair |headquarters = [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], [[Jamaica]] |location = {{JAM}} |membership = |language = [[English language|English]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |num_staff = |budget = |website = [http://www.kingstonbridalweek.com/ Official website] }}
'''Kingston Bridal Week''' is Jamaica’s first and only annual Bridal Week. The event was founded in 2012 by Kibwe McGann, Sean Lyn and Kara-Ann Anderson, and was produced by '''Intuit Concepts'''.<ref name="jamaicaobserver.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/allwoman/kingston-bridal-week_12369528 |title=Jamaica Observer Allwoman News - Kingston Bridal Week - Monday; September 03, 2012 |publisher=jamaicaobserver.com |date=2012-09-03 |accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref> In the second year, Nicola Barbar of Phoenix printery became an official partner and was added to the directorship.<ref>http://www.kingstonbridalweek.com/#!directors/cphn</ref> In September 2013, for the second staging of Kingston Bridal Week, and for the first time in Jamaica,<ref>http://www.huffingtonpost.com/chie-davis/destination-weddingsbig-b_b_4116240.html</ref> Kingston Bridal Week hosted '''Randy Fenoli''',<ref>http://www.tlc.com/tv-shows/randy-to-the-rescue/bios/randy-fenoli-bio.htm</ref> TV star of TLC 's '''Say Yes To The Dress'''<ref>http://www.tlc.com/tv-shows/say-yes-to-the-dress</ref> and '''Randy to the Rescue''' <ref>http://www.tlc.com/tv-shows/randy-to-the-rescue</ref> and author of '''It's all About the Dress''',.<ref>http://www.today.com/id/45149664/ns/today-today_books/t/randy-fenoli-explains-why-its-all-about-dress/#.UfqklmTXhTM</ref>
As part of Kingston Bridal Week's Lifestyle and Honeymoon fashion shows,<ref>http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20120921/social/social1.html</ref> the event has featured international designers Rebacca Ansah (UK), Kesia Eastwick (Barbados), Cedella Marley (Jamaica), Spokes Apparel, Roger Gary (Guyana), and Lubica (Slovakia).<ref>http://www.caribbeanemagazine.com/2012/09/kingston-bridal-week-kbw-heads-to.html</ref>
Kingston Bridal Week has hosted three charity events as part of annual bridal week: In 2012 - a charity dinner in partnership with Angels of Love, A Jamaican charity for children was hosted by international recording artist [[Tami Chynn]], sister of Jamaican singer [[Tessanne Chin]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caribbeancelebs.com/2012/09/11/cc-exclusive-kingston-bridal-week-organizer-kibwe-mcgann-dishes-on-the-exciting-event/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-01-18 |deadurl=no |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130118185705/http://caribbeancelebs.com/2012/09/11/cc-exclusive-kingston-bridal-week-organizer-kibwe-mcgann-dishes-on-the-exciting-event/ |archivedate=2013-01-18 |df= }}</ref> Brides for Haiti, charity dress drive;<ref>http://iriediva.com/2013/09/26/kingston-bridal-week-gives-back-to-young-jamaican-mothers-and-brides-of-haiti/</ref> and '''Baggage Claim''' charity movie premiere.<ref>http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/lifestyle/Countdown-to-Kingston-Bridal-Week_15043841</ref>
